manufacturerProductDescription.media_text: VK-162 G-Mouse USB GPS Dongle Navigation Module Instructions How to use the USB GPS Module 1. Download Driver from website 2. Download U-center software from website 3. Insert USB GPS module to PC, open U-center, choose CoM port and baudrate(default is 9600)

Notes On Using This Module 1:VK-162 GPS support windows Google Earth Raspberry Pi and linux system, not for android and IOS system. It is NOT plug and play for most device. You must install driver before make it work. 2:It is a magntized antenna,if get the GPS signal,please use the GPS module outdoor,If you want to use the GPS module indoor,please install GPS signal amplifier in your room. 3:Once the GPS module is powered on, there is data output,lt usually takes about 40 seconds to be successfully positioned.After the positioning is successful, the correct time, latitude and longitude position data will be available.

VK-162 G-Mouse USB GPS Dongle Navigation Module Instructions Features 1. Data baud rate: 9600 (default) (optional: 4800, 19200, 38400, 57600, 115200, etc.) 2. Data refresh rate: 1Hz-10Hz refresh rate (can be set to output data 1-10 times per second). 3.Built-in Flash, freely configure product baud rate, output statement, output rate, second pulse and other parameters. 4.NMEA-0183 protocol output

The positioning chip used in this module. Low power consumption, high sensitivity. VK-162 G-MOUSE can quickly and accurately locate in places with weak signals such as cities, canyons, under the overhead, and anywhere in the car. The module can be widely used in vehicle monitoring, bus reporting stations, vehicle navigation, ship navigation, notebook navigation and other products.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on November 1, 2023
reviews.reviewText: It is a u-blox, M9 (old) but is very impressive! I connected for about 5 minutes inside of the house, a foot distance from the window. It was picking up the satellites pretty fast (faster than other GPS dongles that I have). I like also the u-center. The price beats everything else.Do I recommend it ? Definitely!

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 11, 2023
reviews.reviewText: Bought this to create a ntp time server. it works like a champ. I tried the Adafruit gpsd node in node red. It works great with this dongle. Its practically plug and play. Gets a 3d fix almost immediately. The long pigtail allows for placement away from the host device. the magnetic base keeps it in place while in motion. all good.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on May 4, 2023
reviews.reviewText: I got one of these to act as a time source for an Inovato Quadra when doing Parks On The Air in areas with no internet connection. This is a Linux based single board computer much like a Raspberry Pi3. I first set it up to work with Chrony and it worked fine. I have since gone to using Conky and it works a treat. I am able to get lock with 15 satellites from in side the house! Very good reciever once you get the software side of things sorted. Will be buying another in the future.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 28, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 4.0 out of 5 stars Works well for it's age.
reviews.reviewText: This is using an older version 7 of U-Blox chips, they are up to version 10 now. It has firmware ver. 1.00 and can't be updated since it has no eprom but still seems to work pretty well. It installed without any problems in Windows 10 running the U-Blox utility u-center and also worked OK in Google Earth. To get it working in Linux is a bit harder and I had to follow the steps shown on the Canada GPS website entitled "How to connect an usb GPS receiver with a Linux computer?" When first setup it takes quite a while to get started since it's data is blank and didn't do much for nearly 3 hours indoors but then it will take right off each time after that so it must have a buile in battery. It also seems to need to be stuck onto a metal surface for best reception.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on September 2, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Great GPS pug
reviews.reviewText: I don't have any problems with this. I use it for the software for tracking weather balloons and their landing. It's very accurate and I've been able to pinpoint weather balloon landing locations by driving almost right to the location it landed at. I can see me on a map to match the weather balloon location is how this tool comes to use. I could also use it with my astronomy equipment but I don't know how. As I can tell it will also be good for that too. I didn't install drivers and I use Windows 11 on a laptop. It may have installed the drivers for me when I plugged it in. It sticks to the roof of my car, but I use it on my dash. It won't stick to anything there, so I got a little clamp to hold wires and used it to hold the GPS pug to the dash. GPS lock seems to be instant. I've never noticed a delay.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on October 27, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 1.0 out of 5 stars It was good while it worked.
reviews.reviewText: Unfortunately, this unit didn't last very long. It used to work well from the edge of my window and usually saw enough satellites to also report altitude. Now, the return window is closed and all it does is spit out empty NMEA sentences, as if it cannot see any satellites at all. It has never been used outside, on a vehicle - only indoors from my windows. I'm disappointed that taking good care of the device didn't help its longevity and I cannot recommend it.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on July 8, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars WORKS... what more can you say?
reviews.reviewText: Priced correctly and works properly. Great for location or time syncing. Ham radio operators may find it perfect for FT8.

reviews.reviewDate: Reviewed in the United States on April 1, 2023
reviews.reviewTitle: 5.0 out of 5 stars Seamless installation on Raspberry Pi 4B
reviews.reviewText: Purchased to set up a Raspberry Pi 4B to use FT8 in the field. I'm having a heck of a time getting the WSJT-X software to work, but this GPS dongle was practically plug-and-play; I followed a few simple steps I found online and it was working within minutes.
No need to download drivers. Just plug n play. I am using it for astronomy. Takes all the guess work out of where you are.
I had a timely delivery and the product is working to my satisfaction. Keep it up.
Connecté à un raspberry pi 3b (stratux) fonctionne immediatement. Acquisition de satellites en qques secondes et stable. Je recommande.
The VK-162 G-Mouse USB GPS Dongle Navigation Module has been an absolute gem for my Raspberry Pi and OpenPlotter setup!

reviews.reviewTitle: Precision a 5 metres, installation automatique, prix imbattable
reviews.reviewText: Sous Windows, installation PlugnPlay (pendant que je cherchais le pilote, belle surprise) et signal capté en secondes. Quelques secondes de plus pour configurer OpenCPN et voila, un systeme de navigation marine portable et indépendent du vieux GPS fixe (nécessitant USB:RS232 connection/conversion). Tres content
